    <Content contentid="4250" contenttypeid="SPA" desc="Spa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Feel like a body scrub or massage? Just ask our staff to bring the spa to you! The beachfront sala at Villa Saanti is an idyllic spot to relax and unwind. We can recommend deluxe treatments carried out by fully trained therapists from a reputable local spa (extra charges will apply). Here’s a sample of what’s on the menu: </p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Thai massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>An ancient traditional art, this method of massage was originally administered on temple grounds by masters with healing abilities. By exerting pressure on specific points of the body and by manipulating muscles and ligaments, the spine is elongated and relieved of tension. The sense of wellbeing as energy and flexibility are brought back into your body is extraordinary. </p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Herbal oil massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Our herbal oil massage – using blends of spice, citrus, aromatic and citronella oils – is a combination of a classic Thai and oil massage. This gentle massage will leave you feeling on top of the world, and is especially suitable for people with little experience of Thai massage. </p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Facial massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>The traditional way of purifying and nourishing your face using natural products, such as our herbal cream cleaner, and honey from the North of Thailand – as well as root masks and soft pressure point massage. This relaxing facial treatment will leave your skin feeling silky smooth, giving you a fresh and healthy glow. Our facial massage is popular with both men and women. </p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Foot massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>This is a treat for one of the body’s most important – and often neglected – parts. After the pressure point massage, herbal foot masque and herbal oil treatment, you’ll be back to full speed again.</p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Manicure &amp; pedicure]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Indulge, sit back and enjoy a quality manicure by a professional therapist. The pedicure includes a luxury foot soak, foot scrub and exfoliation to soften those weary feet. </p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4251" contenttypeid="GYM" desc="Gym">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Keep in shape by following your usual fitness regime in the garden, on the beach (which is also great for jogging or brisk walk), or in the well-equipped gym. Or ask your villa manager to organise a session with our fitness trainer. He can lead hour-long personal training, yoga or Pilates sessions for as many people as you like.</p><p>You can also take lessons in Muay Thai – Thailand’s renowned martial art. It’ll get you fighting fit.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
  </Contents>
